    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
              
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5162</citedRange> (Franz)</bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>65, 4</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>007800</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, p. <citedRange>182</citedRange> and fig. 38</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>55 and 58</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.9</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65033"><name nymRef="#Μνάσαρχος">Μνάσαρχος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64260"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος">Θευχρήστω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"> <note>middle letters <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΣΑ</foreign> now unclear</note></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Mnasarkhos fils de Theukhrestos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Mnasarchos son of Theuchrestos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Mnasarchos figlio di Theuchrestos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>مناسارخوس بن ثيوخريستوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the whole family, see <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/></bibl> and his hietherto unublished Prosopographia. This base might also be some decades later and belong to the grandson of Theuchrestos I.</p>
                <p>The stone was recut and probably reused at the place where Pacho saw it. However it is almost sure that it has once stood in the Mnesarchi tomb N 171 with the other bases of that family.</p> 
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
